'''Cast Paper''' is a [[Paper craft|paper crafting technique]] in which paper fiber or pulp, such as [[Cotton paper|cotton fiber paper]], is formed using a mold. The pulp may consist of pure fiber, or be an amalgam of fiber, binder, and filler, such as [[Papier-mâché]].   The technique is employed for in-the-round sculpture as well as [[bas-relief]].

